#T_SP=webanno.custom.Referent|entity|infstat

#Text=Who was that ?
#Text=It was Brendan Stroud at the time , who was coaching the Dandenong Rangers women 's team .
#Text=I just happened to cross him at Northland , the shopping centre .
#Text=And he said : " Why do n't you come out and play for Dandenong ? "
#Text=I was looking fit and everything else , so I thought " Okay , I 'll come out to one training session and see how I go . "
#Text=And from there played in the 2008 Women 's National League .
#Text=And was voted MVP — most valuable one-pointer , and all-star five .
#Text=So at that point , in 2009 , after that , they went to Beijing , so I watched Beijing from home , because I was n't involved in the Gliders program .
#Text=I just really came back to do women 's league .

#Text=In 2009 , I received some phone calls from the coaching staff , John Trescari , who was coaching the Gliders at that point , who invited me back in to the Glider 's training program , about February , and I said I would come to the one camp and see how I went .
#Text=And went to the one camp and then got selected to go to Canada .
#Text=So , since then I 've been back in the team .
#Text=Back in the Gliders again .
#Text=Yeah !
#Text=And of course you got selected for 2012 ...
#Text=Yes .
#Text=My recollection is that you were n't on the court a great deal , but there was a game when you scored five points ?
#Text=Yeah !
#Text=Within a couple of minutes .
#Text=That was against Mexico .
#Text=Yes .
#Text=That was a good win , actually , that one .
#Text=The strange thing was that afterwards the Mexicans were celebrating like they 'd won ...
#Text=Oh yeah !
#Text=It was very strange .

#Text=I guess one of the things that , like , I am in some ways the backup one pointer in some ways , but what gives me my one point classification , because I used to be a two , is my arm , the damage I received , and the quadriplegia from the transverse myelitis .

#Text=So despite the fact I probably shoot more accurately that most people in the team , because I 've just had to learn to shoot , it also slows me down ; I 'm not the quickest in the team for getting up and down the court , because of having trouble with grip and stuff on my right hand to push .
#Text=I push reasonably quick !
#Text=Most people would say I 'm reasonably quick , but when you at me in comparison to , say , the other eleven girls in the team , I am not as quick .
#Text=The speed at which things move is quite astonishing .
#Text=Yeah , and my ability is more in knowing where people want to get to , so I aim to get there first by taking the most direct route . [ laughter ]
